    "title": "Introduction to Fractions",
    "difficulty": "easy",
    "estimatedMinutes": 15,
    "syncBy": null,
    "content": {
      "text": "# Fractions basics\n\nA fraction represents part of a whole. The number on top is the **numerator** (how many parts you have). The number on the bottom is the **denominator** (how many equal parts the whole is divided into).\n\nExample: 3/4 means 3 parts out of 4 equal parts.",
      "audio": null,
      "image": "/two_added_two.png",
      "videoRef": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dQw4w9WgXcQ"
    },
    "practice": [
      {
        "id": "p1",
        "type": "mcq",
        "question": "In the fraction 5/8, what is the denominator?",
        "options": ["5", "8", "13", "40"],
        "correct": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "p2",
        "type": "mcq",
        "question": "How do you read 1/2?",
        "options": ["One two", "One half", "Two ones", "Half one"],
        "correct": 1
      }
    ],
    "assessment": [
      {
        "id": "a1",
        "type": "mcq",
        "question": "Which fraction is greater: 2/3 or 1/3?",
